<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        App Sandbox is enabled in Phase 8 per Claude/implementation-plan.md §9.

        Required entitlements:

        - app-sandbox                      : turn on the sandbox itself.
        - network.client                   : the transcription client calls
                                             user-configured HTTPS endpoints
                                             (Groq, OpenAI, etc.).
        - files.user-selected.read-write   : the user picks Watch + Output
                                             folders via NSOpenPanel; we need
                                             read/write on whatever they pick.
        - files.bookmarks.app-scope        : security-scoped bookmarks survive
                                             relaunch and re-grant access to
                                             the chosen folders.

        Things we deliberately do NOT request:

        - apple-events / temporary-exception.apple-events
            Audio Hijack control happens via spawning /usr/bin/shortcuts (the
            macOS Shortcuts CLI), which runs the user-authored Run/Stop Session
            Shortcut. No Apple Events leave this process.

        - automation.apple-events
            Same reason.

        - device.audio-input
            Audio Hijack owns recording. Jot never touches the audio stack.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.files.bookmarks.app-scope</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Sparkle 2.x sandboxing (Phase 9 follow-up).

        With App Sandbox enabled and SUEnableInstallerLauncherService=YES,
        Sparkle's update helpers publish three mach services that the main
        Jot process needs to look up:

          $(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spks   (Status — Updater → Jot)
          $(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spki   (Installer Interaction — Jot → Autoupdate; sends "begin install")
          $(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spkp   (Progress — Autoupdate → Jot; periodic download/install %)

        v0.1.2 shipped with only -spks and -spkp. Without -spki, Jot's
        connection to Autoupdate's install-command channel failed silently
        (sandbox blocked the mach lookup), Autoupdate waited indefinitely
        for the "go" signal, Jot timed out the status connection ~4 s in,
        and the Sparkle dialog surfaced "An error occurred while running
        the updater". Confirmed via Console.app during a v0.1.2 → v0.1.3
        attempt.

        Reference: https://sparkle-project.org/documentation/sandboxing/
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.temporary-exception.mach-lookup.global-name</key>
    <array>
        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spks</string>
        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spki</string>
        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)-spkp</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
